Wash and dry all produce. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{} and place in oven on upper rack. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve and peel @Shallot{2%tablespoon}, then finely chop until you have 2 TBSP. Pick @Parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems. Finely chop leaves and stems, keeping them separate. Pick 1 tsp @Thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves; reserve sprigs.

Halve @Multicolored Fingerling Potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Toss with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon} and season with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Carefully remove baking sheet from oven and arrange potatoes on it cut-side down, keeping them toward one side of sheet. Nestle half the thyme sprigs amongst potatoes. Roast in oven ~{10%minutes}.

After 10 minutes, remove potatoes from oven and flip, keeping toward one side of sheet. Toss @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper and arrange on other side of sheet. Return to oven and roast until potatoes are tender and broccoli is beginning to char at edges, about ~{20%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, put @Pine Nuts{1%ounce} in a large pan and place over medium-high heat. Toast, tossing often, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}. Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Pat @Sirloin Steak{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest on a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Place same pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot and a drizzle of oil. Cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Beef Demi-Glace{1}, tomatoes, and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer, then remove from heat. Stir in reserved thyme leaves, half the parsley leaves, and @Butter{2%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in any juices released by steak. Once done, remove potatoes and broccoli from oven. Heat broiler to high.

In a #large bowl{}, toss potatoes with @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon} and parsley stems. Sprinkle @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} over broccoli on sheet. Place under broiler to melt, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide steak, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Sprinkle pine nuts over broccoli. Spoon sauce over steak. Top with rest of parsley leaves.

> This one will amaze everyone with steakhouse-quality feast you just whipped up!